# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values.
#
# This single `.env` file is read in two places:
#   1. Vite, at build time — any var prefixed with `VITE_` is inlined into the
#      client bundle (e.g. the Mapbox token below).
#   2. Wrangler, for local `wrangler dev` — it loads `.env` so the same vars are
#      available to the Worker / Durable Object during local development.
#
# For PRODUCTION Worker secrets, do NOT rely on `.env` — set them with
# `wrangler secret put <NAME>` or in the Cloudflare dashboard. (The Mapbox token
# is a public `pk.` publishable token baked into the client bundle, so it is not
# a secret and just needs to be present at build time.)

# Mapbox GL access token — get one at https://account.mapbox.com/access-tokens/
VITE_MAPBOX_TOKEN=pk.your_mapbox_token_here
